article.headline: Wichita St. 64, Indiana St. 58
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. -- Ramon Clemente had 16 points and 12 rebounds and Clevin Hannah scored 14 points to lead Wichita State to its first road win this season, 64-58 over Indiana State on Wednesday night. The Shockers (11-12, 5-7 Missouri Valley) handed the Sycamores their seventh straight loss. Wichita State shot 22-of-52 from the field and 16-of-24 from the free-throw line. The Shockers scored 18 points off turnovers. Harry Marshall scored 18 for Indiana State (4-19, 2-10), which was outrebounded 39-25. Rashad Reed shot 2-of-3 from three-point range for the Sycamores, who led 26-23 at halftime. Indiana State shot 21-of-47 from the field and 11-of-14 from the line.
